heaviest_rainfall.status: 36.8mm of rain was recorded as having fallen on 04 January 2025, marking an exceptional 37.2 hour precipitation event.  At times the rain was falling at 4.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The 10th ranked rain rate was recorded today with a peak rate of 10.1mm per hour, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  9.37mm of rain fell during the storm's 16.6 hours length.  27.0mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: Ranked 10th for lengthiest precipitation event, today's storm spanned 16.6 hours and was characterized by a peak rain intensity of 10.1mm per hour.  9.37mm of rain fell in total.  The longest rain storm on record lasted 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025 when 36.8mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 4.6mm per hour.
